This will pull the data from the database and display in the tabular format.
Note: Two $result has been provided and one has been commented out, both are working condition. Based on the requirement these can be modified.


Thinking you already have table :


Table Creation:
CREATE TABLE `<tablename>` ( 
  `Sl.No` int(3),
  `VPN Name` text,
  `Site_Name` text,
  `Peer_Gateway` text,
  `Peer_GW_IP` text,
  `LoopBack_IP` text,
  `Primary_Site` text,
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1 COMMENT='<comment name>';

Example:
INSERT INTO `<tablename>` VALUES ("1","data1","data2","data3","data4","data5","data6");
